<p data-start="75" data-end="129">When you push your project to GitHub the first time:</p>
<ul data-start="130" data-end="268">
<li data-start="130" data-end="181">
<p data-start="132" data-end="181">GitHub gets a <strong data-start="146" data-end="158">snapshot</strong> of your local files.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="182" data-end="268">
<p data-start="184" data-end="268">After that, <strong data-start="196" data-end="265">any changes you make locally won’t automatically appear on GitHub</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="270" data-end="303">To update GitHub after changes:</p>
