<p data-start="233" data-end="293">Git created a <strong data-start="247" data-end="267">local repository</strong> in your project folder.</p>
<ul data-start="294" data-end="444">
<li data-start="294" data-end="345">
<p data-start="296" data-end="345">Git now <strong data-start="304" data-end="342">tracks changes only in that folder</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="346" data-end="444">
<p data-start="348" data-end="444"><code data-start="348" data-end="359">git add .</code> tells Git: “Hey, track all files in this folder and prepare them to be committed.”</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="446" data-end="542">So <code data-start="449" data-end="460">git add .</code> <strong data-start="461" data-end="490">doesn’t push anything yet</strong>, it only stages files <strong data-start="513" data-end="541">in your local repository</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="544" data-end="547">
