<li data-start="310" data-end="375">
<p data-start="312" data-end="375">Windows normally uses <strong data-start="334" data-end="372">CRLF (Carriage Return + Line Feed)</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="376" data-end="452">
<p data-start="378" data-end="452">Git is warning: “Next time I touch these files, I’ll convert LF → CRLF.”</p>
</li>
<li data-start="453" data-end="667">
<p data-start="455" data-end="667">⚠️ This is <strong data-start="466" data-end="482">not an error</strong>, it’s just a warning. The <code data-start="509" data-end="520">git add .</code> command is still working—it’s just taking a little longer for all the files in <code data-start="600" data-end="630">lib/mysql-connector-j-9.4.0/</code> because they are many small files.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="669" data-end="672">
<h3 data-start="674" data-end="713"><strong data-start="678" data-end="713">How to fix / avoid the warnings</strong></h3>
<ol data-start="714" data-end="784">
<li data-start="714" data-end="784">
<p data-start="717" data-end="784"><strong data-start="717" data-end="757">Globally ignore line ending warnings</strong> (recommended for Windows):</p>
